# Module Maker — AI Context Summary

This Laravel {{ laravelVersion }} application (PHP {{ phpVersion }}) uses **jackwander/laravel-module-maker v{{ packageVersion }}**.
Features live in isolated modules under `{{ modulesPath }}` using the `{{ rootNamespace }}\{Module}` namespace.
{{ bridgeNote }}

## Non-negotiable rules

1. NEVER hand-create files inside modules — always use the `jw:*` generators (or the `run_generator` MCP tool). They enforce naming, namespaces, and parent classes.
2. New feature = `php artisan jw:make-module {Name}`, then `php artisan jw:make-model {Model} --module={Name} -a` per entity.
3. Models: singular StudlyCase. Tables: plural snake_case. Seeders/Factories/Policies/Observers: singular + suffix.
4. Business logic belongs in the module Service (repository-style, extends the configured BaseService) — controllers stay thin.
5. Validation via FormRequests (`jw:make-request`); API output via Resources (`jw:make-resource`).
6. Module routes live in `{Module}/Routes/api.php` and are auto-prefixed `{{ apiPrefix }}/{module}` — never edit the app-level route files for module endpoints.
7. Maintain `$fillable` on every model — services use it for update filtering and search columns.
8. Tooling detected: {{ toolingLine }}. Run `{{ testCommand }}` before finishing any task.

